Subject: [PATCH] Suppress argument mismatch warnings for gfortran 10+

Add -Wno-argument-mismatch flag to suppress type/rank mismatch warnings
in MPI calls. The -fallow-argument-mismatch flag (already present) allows
compilation despite these mismatches, but still emits warnings. Adding
-Wno-argument-mismatch suppresses the warning output for cleaner builds.

These mismatches are intentional when using MUMPS with -fdefault-integer-8
as the interface uses explicit INTEGER(4) types.

Files:
- cmake/compilers.cmake

--- a/cmake/compilers.cmake
+++ b/cmake/compilers.cmake
@@ -49,7 +49,7 @@ elseif(CMAKE_Fortran_COMPILER_ID STREQUAL "GNU")
 elseif(CMAKE_Fortran_COMPILER_ID STREQUAL "GNU")
   add_compile_options(
   $<$<COMPILE_LANGUAGE:Fortran>:-fimplicit-none>
-  "$<$<AND:$<VERSION_GREATER_EQUAL:${CMAKE_Fortran_COMPILER_VERSION},10>,$<COMPILE_LANGUAGE:Fortran>>:-fallow-argument-mismatch;-fallow-invalid-boz;-fno-strict-aliasing>"
+  "$<$<AND:$<VERSION_GREATER_EQUAL:${CMAKE_Fortran_COMPILER_VERSION},10>,$<COMPILE_LANGUAGE:Fortran>>:-fallow-argument-mismatch;-Wno-argument-mismatch;-fallow-invalid-boz;-fno-strict-aliasing>"
   )

   if(NOT CMAKE_CROSSCOMPILING AND NOT CRAY)

